{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place shallots in mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add 5 g olive oil and cook <b>3 min\/90°C\/speed <b>.","Add cognac, pink peppercorns and sour cream. Without measuring cup, reduce <b>15 min\/90°C\/speed <b>. Leave to cool for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat grill to 230°C and butter 6 gratin dishes.","Heat 1 Tbsp oil in a frying pan and fry prawns with 2 pinches of salt and 1 pinch of pepper until prawns are pink all over. Divide prawns between prepared gratin dishes.","Once sauce has cooled for 15 minutes, <strong>insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Add chives, egg yolks and remaining 1 pinch salt then whisk <b>15 sec\/speed 4<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong> then pour sauce over prawns. Grill for 4 minutes (230°C) until lightly browned and bubbling.","Serve hot, with bread and a side salad if desired."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 shallots, halved (approx. 30 g)","5 g olive oil plus 1 Tbsp","1 tsp cognac","1 tsp pink peppercorns","300 g sour cream","butter, for greasing","400 g peeled, raw prawns","3 pinches fine sea salt, or to taste","1 pinch ground black pepper, or to taste","1 Tbsp fresh chives, chopped","2 egg yolks, from large eggs"]}],"id":"r122586","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-8OwLzSGPt-E\/XZWZZ1a_kyI\/AAAAAAAAeMc\/0UxiMPwnBVod5-hphKqI_e7sOOIWbU6fwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_aXgT183YtAV448nj.png","title":"Prawn Gratin with Pink Peppercorns","publishedAt":"2016-10-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"13.6 g","fat":"16.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"2.7 g","calories":"908 kJ \/ 217 kcal"},"usefulItems":"gratin dish (40 x 25 x 6 cm) or 6 small gratin dishes, frying pan, grill, hob","basicInfo":["easy","5m","30m","6 portions"]}